challenges.description:
This program has a classic buffer overflow vulnerability. Exploit it to gain control of the execution flow and retrieve the flag.

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

void secret() {
    printf("Flag: flag{buff3r_0v3rfl0w_pwn3d}\n");
}

int main() {
    char buffer[64];
    gets(buffer);
    return 0;
}
```
